THE AIRCRAFT CRASHED INTO A BASKETBALL COURT IMMEDIATELY AFTER TAKEOFF 
FROM GLENWOOD SPRINGS ARPT. THE PILOT MADE A TOUCH AND GO LANDING AND 
TURNED OFF THE CARBURETOR HEAT 100 FEET ABOVE THE GROUND DURING THE 
TAKEOFF CLIMB. HE SAID THE ENGINE BEGAN TO RUN ROUGH WHEN THE 
CARBURETOR HEAT WAS PUSHED IN. WHILE ADJUSTING THE MIXTURE CONTROL, 
THE ENGINE LOST POWER. THE AIRCRAFEET STALLED 50 FEET ABOVE THE GROUND AND 
BROKE INTO 3 PIECES ON GROUND IMPACT. THE MIXTURE CONTROL WAS FOUND IN 
THE LEAN POSITION AFTER THE ACCIDENT. 
